    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-06-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <head>228. Memorandum From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1"
                        >Vance</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1"
                        >Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d228fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Subject File, Box 21, Evening Reports
                        (State), 6/79. Secret. <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>
                        initialed the memorandum and wrote: “<persName corresp="#p_VCR_1"
                            >Cy</persName>.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-06-04">June 4, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to Panama.]</p>
                <p>(2) Panama—<persName corresp="#p_LGG_1">Gabriel Lewis</persName> told us last
                    night that <persName corresp="#p_THO_1">Torrijos</persName> believed <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGA_1">Somoza</persName> was on his last legs and wanted to
                    deliver the <hi rend="italic">coup de grace.</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_THO_1">Torrijos</persName> is apparently supplying arms
                    deliveries daily to the Sandinistas in southern Nicaragua. <persName
                        corresp="#p_LGG_1">Lewis</persName> intimated that <persName
                        corresp="#p_THO_1">Torrijos</persName> now wants to recognize a “Sandinista
                    government.” <persName corresp="#p_LGG_1">Lewis</persName> asked for someone to
                    come to Panama to calm <persName corresp="#p_THO_1">Torrijos</persName> down,
                    and Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MAH_1">Moss</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_PRA_1">Bob Pastor</persName> flew to Panama today to try to do
                        that.<note n="2" xml:id="d228fn2">See <ref target="#d230">Document
                        230</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>(3) <persName corresp="#p_MJM_1">Murphy</persName>—Congressman Murphy is voicing
                    concern over Panama’s involvement with the Sandinistas and the charges that
                    Panama is equipping the guerrillas.<note n="3" xml:id="d228fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote in the left margin:
                        “I’ll call <persName corresp="#p_MJM_1">Murphy</persName>.” See <ref
                            target="#d229">Document 229</ref>.</note> He says he will hold hearings
                    on the subject later in the week, which will further complicate the problems
                    facing the Treaty implementation legislation. We ought to try and get the
                    leadership to turn it off or postpone it.<note n="4" xml:id="d228fn4">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> placed an arrow in the left
                        margin and wrote: “Do so.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to Panama.]</p>
            </div>
